<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="434" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,223,430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,259,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="434">Comment.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1826" box="[334,438,259,285]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,438,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="434">Zodarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with 175 nominal species, is the second largest genus in the family and the largest in 
<taxonomicName authority="(WSC 2022)" baseAuthorityName="WSC" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[151,419,295,321]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Zodariinae">
Zodariinae (
<bibRefCitation author="WSC" box="[284,411,295,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" refId="ref6756" refString="WSC (2022) World Spider Catalog. Version 23.0. Natural History Museum Bern, Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 2 June 2022) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="url" year="2022">WSC 2022</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.It is restricted to the West Palaearctic, with most of the species known from the Mediterranean region (
<bibRefCitation author="WSC" box="[241,375,331,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" refId="ref6756" refString="WSC (2022) World Spider Catalog. Version 23.0. Natural History Museum Bern, Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 2 June 2022) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="url" year="2022">WSC 2022</bibRefCitation>
). Judging from the diverse conformations in the copulatory organs of the species currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1826" box="[283,387,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,387,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="434">Zodarion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genus is not monophyletic, with species closely related to the generotype restricted to the Eastern Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M." box="[420,703,403,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="434" pagination="145 - 193" refId="ref6801" refString="Zamani, A. &amp; Marusik, Y. M. (2021) Revision of the spider family Zodariidae (Arachnida, Araneae) in Iran and Turkmenistan, with seventeen new species. ZooKeys, 1035, 145 - 193. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 1035.65767" type="journal article" year="2021">Zamani &amp; Marusik 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
